 A Non-Interventional Study on the Tolerability and Efficacy of Octagam 5% or 10% or panzyga.

 Patients with any indication (replacement and immonomodulation) as prescribed by the treating physician.

 Marketed Octagam 5% or 10% or panzyga will be used according to the investigator prescription; intravenous (iv) administration.

The primary objective is to detect and evaluate adverse drug reactions (ADRs) occurring during or after the administration of Octagam or panzyga in any indication, age group or treatment regimen, where a causal relationship to the administration of Octagam or panzyga is suspected.

